import React from 'react'; import { Container, Row, Col, Card } from 'react-bootstrap'; import { useSpring, animated } from 'react-spring'; import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css'; const EBeam = () => { const fadeIn = useSpring({ from: { opacity: 0 }, to: { opacity: 1 }, config: { duration: 1000 }, }); return (

Electron-Beam Lithography Tool

{/* Overview Card */} Overview Our electron-beam lithography tool enables the precise fabrication of nanoscale patterns on silicon wafers. It involves shooting electrons through carbon nanotubes, focusing the beam, and exposing a silicon wafer covered with a photoresist chemical. Subsequent development dissolves the exposed parts, allowing the creation of customizable patterns and electrical circuits on a nanoscale. {/* Task Cards */} Electronics We are currently testing and developing the current sensing system to track the electron flow through the system. Software (Back End) Development of software that translates nanoscale patterns into a sequence of silicon wafer and electron-beam actuations. Connection with the picomotor for wafer movement is underway. Software (Front End) Creation of a user-friendly GUI to draw the desired patterns, connected to the back-end system for seamless integration. Theoretical Simulation (COMSOL + Theory) Simulation of electron beam flow in COMSOL to predict focal length and spot size. Comparison with a theoretical simulator created in-house by Matty, head of the E-Beam team, for validation. Theoretical Simulation (Custom Software) Development of custom software to simulate the end-to-end behavior of the entire system. {/* Page Under Construction Card */} Page Under Construction Please note that this page is under construction. We'll update it with more information and progress updates. ); }; export default EBeam;
